01:11:52,192 --> 01:11:54,125
you need to care a little bit
more about what he does.

1450
01:11:54,160 --> 01:11:56,094
-I do care.
-Oh. Pfft.

1451
01:11:56,129 --> 01:11:58,529
I don't.

1452
01:11:58,565 --> 01:12:02,166
But I'm just so...
I mean, I do. I do.

1453
01:12:02,202 --> 01:12:04,135
-I just, I just don't get it.
-Really?

1454
01:12:04,170 --> 01:12:07,839
He's not asking you to get it.

1455
01:12:07,874 --> 01:12:10,007
All he wants you to do is just

1456
01:12:10,043 --> 01:12:13,678
accept the path
that he's chosen.

1457
01:12:13,713 --> 01:12:14,946
That's it.

1458
01:12:16,683 --> 01:12:20,184
Okay. My turn.

1459
01:12:20,220 --> 01:12:22,320
Brittney doesn't like me either,
does she?

1460
01:12:22,355 --> 01:12:23,321
Nah, not really.

1461
01:12:23,356 --> 01:12:25,656
-Oh. Damn.
-No.

1462
01:12:25,692 --> 01:12:28,092
-Girl, we gotta fix this. Yeah.
-Pretty much.

1463
01:12:30,263 --> 01:12:32,130
[knocking on door]

1464
01:12:32,165 --> 01:12:34,165
Where's your drinking buddy?

1465
01:12:34,200 --> 01:12:37,268
-I've been avoiding her all day.
-Cute.

1466
01:12:39,339 --> 01:12:41,038
[sighs]

1467
01:12:41,074 --> 01:12:44,075
She's downstairs in the kitchen
with my mother.

1468
01:12:44,110 --> 01:12:48,012
I actually think
I overheard them making up.

1469
01:12:52,886 --> 01:12:54,886
Are we ready for this?

1470
01:12:54,921 --> 01:12:58,523
I mean, really ready?

1471
01:13:00,293 --> 01:13:02,193
Yeah. Yeah, I am.

1472
01:13:04,631 --> 01:13:06,130
Are you?

1473
01:13:07,233 --> 01:13:08,900
Yeah.

1474
01:13:08,935 --> 01:13:10,234
But you have to answer
your phone.

1475
01:13:10,270 --> 01:13:13,104
-Oh, done.
-No, I'm serious.

1476
01:13:13,139 --> 01:13:14,906
You know, sometimes
you just have to be present

1477
01:13:14,941 --> 01:13:17,041
and have a plan.

1478
01:13:21,147 --> 01:13:22,980
Am I turning into my mother?

1479
01:13:25,084 --> 01:13:27,618
Like, planning a wedding
is hard.

1480
01:13:27,654 --> 01:13:29,754
I wasn't prepared to do this
by myself.

1481
01:13:29,789 --> 01:13:31,355
Well, I thought
that's what you wanted to do.

1482
01:13:31,391 --> 01:13:34,225
It's bigger than the wedding,
Amiri.

1483
01:13:34,260 --> 01:13:37,762
I'm talking about our future.

1484
01:13:37,797 --> 01:13:40,598
You know, I love that you march
to the beat of your own drum,

1485
01:13:40,633 --> 01:13:45,870
but you have to make sure that
I'm there marching with you.

1486
01:13:45,905 --> 01:13:48,072
You know, this whole time I've
been trying not to be my mother

1487
01:13:48,107 --> 01:13:52,343
and be this carefree spirit,
but it's not me.

1488
01:13:54,447 --> 01:13:59,116
But that's what I love
about our love.

1489
01:13:59,152 --> 01:14:00,885
Our differences give us
the balance we need

1490
01:14:00,920 --> 01:14:05,223
to grow into whatever we want.

1491
01:14:05,258 --> 01:14:08,926
That was,
that was really beautiful.

1492
01:14:13,433 --> 01:14:16,934
But you sound
like a fortune cookie.

1493
01:14:16,970 --> 01:14:18,736
[laughing]

1494
01:14:18,771 --> 01:14:20,238
I'm just playing.

1495
01:14:20,273 --> 01:14:22,607
-I love you.
-I love you, too.

1496
01:14:28,848 --> 01:14:31,816
-So we're gonna do it.
-Hell, yeah, we're gonna do it.

1497
01:14:31,851 --> 01:14:32,950
[laughs]

1498
01:14:32,986 --> 01:14:36,120
[instrumental music]

1499
01:15:05,051 --> 01:15:06,484
[knocking on door]

1500
01:15:06,519 --> 01:15:10,121
-Hey there.
-Hey.

1501
01:15:10,156 --> 01:15:11,155
Brittney,
I feel like an old fool.

1502
01:15:11,190 --> 01:15:13,057
-No.
-I should've never...

1503
01:15:13,092 --> 01:15:17,028
Mom, I'm really sorry.

1504
01:15:17,063 --> 01:15:18,996
-You're sorry?
-Yeah.

1505
01:15:21,401 --> 01:15:24,735
You know,
I've just been so worried

1506
01:15:24,771 --> 01:15:26,037
about you over-crowding me

1507
01:15:26,072 --> 01:15:29,173
that I guess I never stopped

1508
01:15:29,208 --> 01:15:32,043
to ask myself why that is.

1509
01:15:32,078 --> 01:15:35,212
Planning a wedding is hard.

1510
01:15:35,248 --> 01:15:36,981
And it's dumb
to do it by myself,

1511
01:15:37,016 --> 01:15:41,018
especially when I have
the greatest coach in my corner

1512
01:15:41,054 --> 01:15:42,486
rooting for me to win.

1513
01:15:43,523 --> 01:15:47,224
Wow. Brittney...

1514
01:15:47,260 --> 01:15:50,194
I'm speechless. I am.

1515
01:15:50,229 --> 01:15:53,497
[sighs]
Thank you.

1516
01:15:53,533 --> 01:15:58,269
Mom, there's so much
that I love about you.

1517
01:15:58,304 --> 01:16:02,873
You're a smart, intelligent,

1518
01:16:02,909 --> 01:16:04,875
nurturing woman.

1519
01:16:04,911 --> 01:16:06,444
[sighs]

1520
01:16:06,479 --> 01:16:09,447
No, mom,
I really, I love our talks.

1521
01:16:09,482 --> 01:16:11,449
And I love the way
that you love on me.

1522
01:16:11,484 --> 01:16:13,551
It's just..

1523
01:16:13,586 --> 01:16:16,554
Mom, you have to trust me

1524
01:16:16,589 --> 01:16:18,956
to grow up a little bit.

1525
01:16:18,992 --> 01:16:23,227
Hey. I get it.

1526
01:16:23,262 --> 01:16:25,463
My butterfly
needs to spread her wings.

1527
01:16:25,498 --> 01:16:28,866
-Just a little bit.
-All right.

1528
01:16:28,901 --> 01:16:31,535
Now, if I do that,
you promise me that you will...

1529
01:16:31,571 --> 01:16:34,572
[inhales] you gotta communicate
with me more.

1530
01:16:34,607 --> 01:16:36,107
-Agreed.
-Okay?

1531
01:16:36,142 --> 01:16:38,476
And consult with me

1532
01:16:38,511 --> 01:16:41,946
when you make
these big decisions.

1533
01:16:41,981 --> 01:16:44,448
Okay. Agreed.

1534
01:16:44,484 --> 01:16:49,053
And promise me I will always be
your girl BFF.

1535
01:16:49,088 --> 01:16:50,488
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

1536
01:16:50,523 --> 01:16:52,323
Okay!

1537
01:16:52,358 --> 01:16:54,258
-I love you.
-Oh.

1538
01:16:56,529 --> 01:16:58,396
I love you, baby.

1539
01:16:59,298 --> 01:17:01,132
Oh.

1540
01:17:01,167 --> 01:17:03,901
My little princess
getting married.

1541
01:17:03,936 --> 01:17:04,919
[instrumental music]

1542
01:17:10,126 --> 01:17:11,492
<i> ♪ Christmas ♪</i>

1543
01:17:14,297 --> 01:17:18,099
<i> ♪ Merry Christmas sugar ♪</i>

1544
01:17:18,134 --> 01:17:20,434
<i> ♪ We're feeling naive ♪</i>

1545
01:17:20,470 --> 01:17:23,371
<i> ♪ Christmas with you girl ♪</i>

1546
01:17:23,406 --> 01:17:25,539
<i> ♪ Merry Christmas ♪</i>

1547
01:17:27,443 --> 01:17:31,712
<i> ♪ Happy happy new year sugar ♪</i>

1548
01:17:31,748 --> 01:17:35,049
<i> ♪ Merry merry merry merry</i>
<i> Christmas ♪</i>

1549
01:17:35,084 --> 01:17:36,550
How are you feelin'?

1550
01:17:37,754 --> 01:17:38,552
-Nervous.
-Yeah?

1551
01:17:38,588 --> 01:17:41,589
-But more excited than ever.
-Good.

1552
01:17:41,624 --> 01:17:44,158
[clears throat]
You look handsome.

1553
01:17:44,193 --> 01:17:46,060
[chuckles]

1554
01:17:46,095 --> 01:17:47,995
[exhales]

1555
01:17:48,030 --> 01:17:50,631
Oh. I have something for you.

1556
01:17:51,634 --> 01:17:52,566
[chuckles]

1557
01:18:00,042 --> 01:18:01,108
[door shuts]

1558
01:18:01,144 --> 01:18:04,078
[instrumental music]

1559
01:18:08,217 --> 01:18:09,417
It's beautiful.

1560
01:18:12,155 --> 01:18:13,254
Hm.

1561
01:18:15,324 --> 01:18:17,258
[sighs] Read it.

1562
01:18:24,467 --> 01:18:27,134
And don't you ever forget it.

1563
01:18:27,170 --> 01:18:31,172
And I'm not only proud of you,
I am so impressed.

1564
01:18:32,341 --> 01:18:34,341
-Impressed?
-I am.

1565
01:18:34,377 --> 01:18:36,644
You know, Jean-Michel Basquiat,

1566
01:18:36,679 --> 01:18:40,181
he came from money and he
denounced his entire inheritance

1567
01:18:40,216 --> 01:18:41,749
to follow his dream.

1568
01:18:43,686 --> 01:18:46,053
You read that on the Internet,
didn't you?

1569
01:18:46,088 --> 01:18:47,588
I did.

1570
01:18:48,591 --> 01:18:50,658
But I'm serious.

1571
01:18:52,595 --> 01:18:55,196
You don't have to live
for me and your father.

1572
01:18:57,266 --> 01:19:01,268
You've earned your right
to walk into your own legacy.

1573
01:19:03,172 --> 01:19:06,040
And your father,

1574
01:19:06,075 --> 01:19:07,641
he would be so proud of you.

1575
01:19:12,715 --> 01:19:14,381
-[chuckles]
-I love you, mom.

1576
01:19:14,417 --> 01:19:16,317
I love you, too, honey.

1577
01:19:17,687 --> 01:19:19,420
I love you.

1578
01:19:19,455 --> 01:19:22,389
[instrumental music]

1579
01:19:35,872 --> 01:19:38,506
-Oh.
-Oh.

1580
01:19:38,541 --> 01:19:40,508
Mom, you're gonna mess up
your makeup.

1581
01:19:40,543 --> 01:19:41,675
Oh.

1582
01:19:41,711 --> 01:19:44,011
You're gonna make me
mess up mine.

1583
01:19:45,715 --> 01:19:47,181
Well...

1584
01:19:49,085 --> 01:19:52,386
I just can't believe
this is happening, baby.

1585
01:19:52,421 --> 01:19:55,289
Oh, you look so beautiful.

1586
01:19:55,324 --> 01:19:57,124
Thank you.

1587
01:19:57,159 --> 01:19:59,059
[sighs]

1588
01:19:59,095 --> 01:20:00,761
You remind me so much of me
on my day,

1589
01:20:00,796 --> 01:20:04,465
it's... kinda scary.

1590
01:20:04,500 --> 01:20:07,401
Oh. Were you nervous?

1591
01:20:07,436 --> 01:20:09,870
Uh, I was fine.

1592
01:20:09,906 --> 01:20:13,741
Now, your father,
hm, he was a wreck.

1593
01:20:16,913 --> 01:20:19,613
You know, I know he really
wanted to be here, Brit.

1594
01:20:19,649 --> 01:20:21,248
-But I...
-[door opens]

1595
01:20:21,284 --> 01:20:22,316
Baby girl!

1596
01:20:22,351 --> 01:20:24,218
-Dad!
-Daddy's here.

1597
01:20:27,423 --> 01:20:28,822
You look beautiful.

1598
01:20:28,858 --> 01:20:30,591
I didn't think
you were gonna make it.

1599
01:20:30,626 --> 01:20:33,594
Oh, come on now.
You know better than that.

1600
01:20:33,629 --> 01:20:34,828
Plus, I need to make sure
the prince

1601
01:20:34,864 --> 01:20:37,264
that's marrying my princess
isn't a fraud.

1602
01:20:37,300 --> 01:20:39,600
[laughs]

1603
01:20:39,635 --> 01:20:41,402
You look beautiful.
This is your day.

1604
01:20:41,437 --> 01:20:44,572
[instrumental music]

1605
01:20:54,483 --> 01:20:57,418
[crowd cheering]

1606
01:20:59,322 --> 01:21:00,754
Yay!

1607
01:21:02,325 --> 01:21:03,757
Oh. Well, thank you.

1608
01:21:08,731 --> 01:21:10,764
Ah!

1609
01:21:14,303 --> 01:21:15,302
[glass clinking]

1610
01:21:15,338 --> 01:21:16,704
[chuckles]

1611
01:21:16,739 --> 01:21:18,639
Um, Walt, can we turn that up?

1612
01:21:18,674 --> 01:21:19,607
Put some reverb on that.

1613
01:21:19,642 --> 01:21:21,442
[laughs] Thank you.

1614
01:21:21,477 --> 01:21:24,478
So, Amiri.

1615
01:21:24,513 --> 01:21:27,881
[sighs] I can still remember
when you were a little boy

1616
01:21:27,917 --> 01:21:31,318
and you would get so frustrated
with puzzles,

1617
01:21:31,354 --> 01:21:36,190
that you would just
force the pieces together.

1618
01:21:36,225 --> 01:21:37,791
Well, Brittney, you are

1619
01:21:37,827 --> 01:21:41,562
the perfect piece
to his puzzle.

1620
01:21:41,597 --> 01:21:44,798
He no longer
has to force things to fit.

1621
01:21:46,936 --> 01:21:50,204
-To the bride and groom.
-To the bride and groom.

1622
01:21:50,239 --> 01:21:51,372
[applauding]

1623
01:21:51,407 --> 01:21:52,806
Yeah.

1624
01:21:52,842 --> 01:21:54,708
Yes! Lovely.

1625
01:21:54,744 --> 01:21:56,810
I didn't know we were doing
shout-outs. Hey-hey!

1626
01:21:56,846 --> 01:21:59,713
[laughs] You know, Brittney,

1627
01:21:59,749 --> 01:22:02,650
you are the apple of my eye,

1628
01:22:02,685 --> 01:22:06,220
my cherry pumpkin piece of pie.

1629
01:22:06,255 --> 01:22:10,924
And, uh, Amiri,
well, I now have the pleasure

1630
01:22:10,960 --> 01:22:14,662
of watching you
be the fruit of her loom.

1631
01:22:15,965 --> 01:22:18,198
'Cause he's a groom.

1632
01:22:18,234 --> 01:22:22,870
And here's
to your storybook of a journey.

1633
01:22:22,905 --> 01:22:27,841
-To the bride and groom!
-[all] To the bride and groom!

1634
01:22:27,877 --> 01:22:30,244
-[indistinct chatter]
-Thank you.

1635
01:22:30,279 --> 01:22:31,979
[Demetria] Yup.
[Tanya] What are you doing?

1636
01:22:33,983 --> 01:22:37,217
You can sit, you can sit down.
Sit down right there.

1637
01:22:37,253 --> 01:22:39,219
-You can sit...
-I know where my seat is.

1638
01:22:39,255 --> 01:22:41,789
Well, she's so funny.
Oh, yeah, sit down.

1639
01:22:41,824 --> 01:22:46,694
Okay, so I wanna add a quote
to that storybook

1640
01:22:46,729 --> 01:22:49,430
from my good friend,

1641
01:22:49,465 --> 01:22:52,032
Toni Morrison.

1642
01:22:52,068 --> 01:22:53,901
-May she rest...
-Personal, personal space.

1643
01:22:53,936 --> 01:22:56,303
-Yeah. Personal friend. Yeah.
-Oh, good.

1644
01:22:56,338 --> 01:22:59,573
Yeah. Yes.
You know, God rest her soul.

1645
01:22:59,608 --> 01:23:03,944
"Love is divine only,

1646
01:23:03,979 --> 01:23:05,813
difficult always.

1647
01:23:05,848 --> 01:23:09,049
And if you believe it is easy,
you are a fool.

1648
01:23:09,085 --> 01:23:13,954
If you think it is natural,
you are blind."

1649
01:23:15,624 --> 01:23:18,726
[laughs]
Amiri, Brittney...

1650
01:23:20,429 --> 01:23:24,765
uh, you know, I-I think
you should and-and you would

1651
01:23:24,800 --> 01:23:29,837
turn each page of your storybook
with intention.

1652
01:23:29,872 --> 01:23:32,039
-[indistinct chatter]
-[applauding]

1653
01:23:33,008 --> 01:23:35,642
Yes. All right. Yes.

1654
01:23:35,678 --> 01:23:37,911
Ooh, you got it bad.

1655
01:23:37,947 --> 01:23:39,613
-Excuse me, lady.
-Oh. All right.

1656
01:23:39,648 --> 01:23:41,482
Okay, now you can find
your seat

1657
01:23:41,517 --> 01:23:42,416
and you can sit in it.

1658
01:23:42,451 --> 01:23:43,684
[laughing]

1659
01:23:43,719 --> 01:23:46,687
Go, girl. All right.

1660
01:23:46,722 --> 01:23:50,924
You know what, speaking of Toni,
Toni Morrison,

1661
01:23:50,960 --> 01:23:52,793
you know,
right before she passed,

1662
01:23:52,828 --> 01:23:55,496
we were actually
supposed to go horseback riding.

1663
01:23:55,531 --> 01:23:56,530
-Mm.
-Yes.

1664
01:23:56,565 --> 01:23:58,932
-She hated horses.
-No.

1665
01:23:58,968 --> 01:24:01,034
But she loved to ride 'em. Okay.

1666
01:24:01,070 --> 01:24:05,906
[laughs] But before she passed,
she said...

1667
01:24:07,143 --> 01:24:09,042
Oh, I got this. Thank you.

1668
01:24:09,078 --> 01:24:13,714
[laughs] She said,
"The function of freedom

1669
01:24:13,749 --> 01:24:16,483
is to free someone else."

1670
01:24:16,519 --> 01:24:18,786
If you free your mind,
the rest will follow.

1671
01:24:18,821 --> 01:24:21,054
-All right, mom.
-Yes, okay.

1672
01:24:21,090 --> 01:24:22,623
Don't be color-blind.

1673
01:24:22,658 --> 01:24:24,858
-You talk about being black...
-Let me... Can I...

1674
01:24:24,894 --> 01:24:26,660
Uh, no, you can't, you can't.
No, you can't.

1675
01:24:26,695 --> 01:24:30,464
Uh, if you ladies would please
go back to your seats?

1676
01:24:30,499 --> 01:24:32,466
[indistinct chatter]

1677
01:24:32,501 --> 01:24:34,668
-Um, your seats.
-Okay.

1678
01:24:34,703 --> 01:24:36,136
Ms. Hamilton, mom?

1679
01:24:36,172 --> 01:24:38,539
-Love you.
-Mm-hmm.

1680
01:24:38,574 --> 01:24:40,841
Mm...
Love you, baby.

1681
01:24:40,876 --> 01:24:42,843
Everybody, please give it up
for my mom

1682
01:24:42,878 --> 01:24:44,511
and my beautiful mother-in-law.

1683
01:24:44,547 --> 01:24:46,013
Thank you.

1684
01:24:46,048 --> 01:24:49,049
I would like to share
a few words about my wife,

1685
01:24:49,084 --> 01:24:50,884
the bride at this wedding,
if that's okay.

1686
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:52,052
[laughs]

1687
01:24:55,057 --> 01:24:56,023
Brittney...

1688
01:24:57,793 --> 01:25:00,594
I could study under Basquiat,

1689
01:25:00,629 --> 01:25:02,930
Picasso and Van Gogh

1690
01:25:02,965 --> 01:25:05,766
and still never create
a work of art

1691
01:25:05,801 --> 01:25:07,534
as beautiful as you.

1692
01:25:07,570 --> 01:25:09,069
[woman] Oh...

1693
01:25:09,104 --> 01:25:12,906
You're my sun, my moon.

1694
01:25:12,942 --> 01:25:16,944
And I love you
like the fat kid loves cake.

1695
01:25:16,979 --> 01:25:19,847
[applauding]

1696
01:25:19,882 --> 01:25:22,983
[instrumental music]

1697
01:25:30,893 --> 01:25:32,226
You wanna go out there?

1698
01:25:32,261 --> 01:25:34,895
Uh, maybe later.

1699
01:25:34,930 --> 01:25:37,664
Looks like
